{
  "id": "indus_cas_sign_roles",
  "name": "Indus CISI: CPSC Sign Role Classification (CASIndusEngine)",
  "description": "Uses the CASIndusEngine — our custom engine built on CPSC IterativeEngine. For each sign in the CISI corpus: observes I/M/T rates from real Mohenjo-daro inscription sequences, then builds a CasModel with Dravidian morphological constraints (case suffixes terminal-biased, determinatives initial-biased, phonetic syllables medial-biased). CPSC projects each sign's observed rates onto this constraint manifold to produce principled role classifications. BuiltinLM(dravidian) provides phoneme candidate matching for terminal (case suffix) and initial (determinative) signs. This is a fundamentally different approach from black-box SA: constraints are transparent, user-editable in the CAS Models editor.",
